main event: A civilian reported seeing a metallic, cigar-shaped object that moved erratically over Memphis, Tennessee on November 16, 1968.
interesting points: The object was described as being brighter than the surrounding sky and moving jerkily across the field of vision, changing direction rapidly.
The object was approximately the size of a quarter held at arm's length.
No sound was heard, and there were no other objects in the field of view.
The Naval Air Station at Millington, Tennessee reportedly picked up the object on radar and it maneuvered over the Memphis area.
Several people reported seeing the object, but no photographs or other physical evidence was obtained to corroborate the sightings.
photographs: no, the report does not include any photographs
